question:
District category contains Financial District, Manufacturing District, Government Complex, and Automotive District.
Supermarkets category contains Aldi, Stop & Shop, Loblaws, and Family Dollar.
Product category contains Rice Cakes, Flavored Water, Nuts, and Canned Tomatoes.
Ingredient category contains Shortening, Olive Oil, Sunflower Oil, and Bulgur.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Nuts equals each Loblaws 's Ingredient.
The number of each Nuts 's Sunflower Oil equals each Automotive District 's Family Dollar.
The number of each Canned Tomatoes 's Bulgur equals each Family Dollar 's Flavored Water.
The number of each Rice Cakes 's Sunflower Oil equals each Aldi 's Canned Tomatoes.
The number of each Automotive District 's Family Dollar equals 2.
The number of each Loblaws 's Flavored Water equals 21.
The number of each Family Dollar 's Flavored Water equals the sum of each Stop & Shop 's Nuts and each Financial District 's Ingredient.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Stop & Shop equals 5.
The number of each Flavored Water 's Olive Oil equals each Loblaws 's Flavored Water.
The number of each Aldi 's Canned Tomatoes equals each Automotive District 's Family Dollar.
The number of each Family Dollar 's Rice Cakes equals 19 times the difference of each Family Dollar 's Flavored Water and each Government Complex 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Financial District 's Loblaws equals the sum of each Stop & Shop 's Product, each Flavored Water 's Olive Oil, each Stop & Shop 's Nuts, and each Loblaws 's Ingredient.
The number of each Government Complex 's Family Dollar equals 12 more than each Automotive District 's Family Dollar.
How many Product does Stop & Shop have?
solution:
Define each Loblaws 's Flavored Water as v; So v = 21.
Define each Flavored Water 's Olive Oil as P; So P = v = 21.
Define each Flavored Water 's Ingredient as x; So x = P = 21.
Define each Loblaws 's Ingredient as l; l = x * v = 21 * 21 = 4.
Define each Stop & Shop 's Nuts as g; So g = l = 4.
Define each Stop & Shop 's Product as n; So n = g = 4.
